investigation.title: Transcriptional profiling of the mutualistic bacterium Vibrio fischeri and an hfq mutant under modeled microgravity
investigation.description: For long-duration space missions, it is critical to maintain health-associated homeostasis between astronauts and their microbiome. To achieve this goal it is important to more fully understand the host–symbiont relationship under the physiological stress conditions of spaceflight.

project.title: Impact of Microgravity on the Cell-CelInteractions between a Mutualistic Bacterium and Its Animal Host
